"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s19",
"title":{
"__html":"Irritable Bowel Syndrome"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"5b7f79",
"children":[
"Irritable Bowel Syndrome"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s19_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"bb12bc",
"children":[
"Diagnosis requires recurrent abdominal pain at least 1 day per week for 3 months, as well as at least two of the following:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ab016c",
"children":[
"defecation-related pain"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e98740",
"children":[
"change in stool frequency"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ad9593",
"children":[
"change in stool consistency"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2d2e5c",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"irritable bowel syndrome",
"children":[
"IBS"
]
},
" can be further subtyped to include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4c0fb7",
"children":[
"predominant constipation (IBS-C)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"3c4b86",
"children":[
"predominant diarrhea (IBS-D)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9c6053",
"children":[
"mixed bowel habits (IBS-M)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3129dc",
"children":[
"In patients with IBS-D, test for celiac disease and giardiasis, and obtain fecal calprotectin to differentiate from ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"inflammatory bowel disease",
"children":[
"IBD"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"99de51",
"children":[
"In the absence of alarm symptoms, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"complete blood count",
"children":[
"CBC"
]
},
","
]
},
" serum chemistry studies, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"thyroid-stimulating hormone",
"children":[
"TSH"
]
},
","
]
},
" and abdominal imaging are unnecessary."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"106d33",
"children":[
"Screening colonoscopy should be pursued only in patients who otherwise meet criteria for colon cancer screening."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c3f1aa",
"children":[
"Patients with severe or refractory symptoms require diagnostic colonoscopy."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s19_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1d6113",
"children":[
"Management of IBS focuses on controlling symptoms rather than on cure."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ec0e03",
"children":[
"For all patients:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"65b9a9",
"children":[
"avoidance of gluten (even in absence of celiac disease); dairy products; and fermentable oligosaccharides, disaccharides, monosaccharides, and polyols (",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"fermentable oligosaccharides, disaccharides, monosaccharides, and polyols",
"children":[
"FODMAPs"
]
},
")"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"d0b765",
"children":[
"dicyclomine and peppermint oil for abdominal pain and global symptoms"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"51354d",
"children":[
"For ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"irritable bowel syndrome with constipation",
"children":[
"IBS-C"
]
},
":"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1851f1",
"children":[
"polyethylene glycol (PEG)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"482254",
"children":[
"lubiprostone, linaclotide, and plecanatide if refractory to ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"polyethylene glycol",
"children":[
"PEG"
]
}
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e3fa56",
"children":[
"For ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"irritable bowel syndrome with diarrhea",
"children":[
"IBS-D"
]
},
":"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"3668df",
"children":[
"loperamide"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7831d1",
"children":[
"tricyclic antidepressants"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b0a819",
"children":[
"rifaximin, eluxadoline, and alosetron for refractory symptoms"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"90d0fa",
"children":[
"Alosetron should not be used as first-line therapy for IBS-D because of the risk of ischemic colitis."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
},
